Package fr.xephi.authme.command

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ExecutableCommand
    Base class for AuthMe commands that can be executed.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CommandArgumentDescription
    Wrapper for the description of a command argument.
    CommandDescription
    Command description â€“ defines which labels ("names") will lead to a command and points to the ExecutableCommand implementation that executes the logic of the command.
    CommandDescription.CommandBuilder
    Builder for initializing CommandDescription objects.
    CommandHandler
    The AuthMe command handler, responsible for invoking the correct ExecutableCommand based on incoming command labels or for displaying a help message for unknown command labels.
    CommandInitializer
    Initializes all available AuthMe commands.
    CommandMapper
    Maps incoming command parts to the correct CommandDescription.
    CommandUtils
    Utility functions for CommandDescription objects.
    FoundCommandResult
    Result of a command mapping by CommandHandler.
    PlayerCommand
    Common base type for player-only commands, handling the verification that the command sender is indeed a player.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    FoundResultStatus
    Result status for mapping command parts.
